# Knowledge directory boundary (`lib/features/knowledge/`)

## Authority

- `#features/knowledge` is the substrate for organization-scoped knowledge ingestion and retrieval.
- `#features/lynx` is the product surface and consumes knowledge only through the `#features/knowledge` barrel.
- `app/` route files compose UI and handlers only; data and domain logic stay in `lib/features/knowledge/**`.

## Internal subdomains (conceptual; filename-prefix enforced)

- Ingestion files: `data/source-*`, `data/pipeline-*`, `data/source-sync.workflow.ts`, `actions/*-source.ts`
- Retrieval files: `data/retrieve-*`, `data/eval-*`, `actions/run-eval-set.ts`
- Governance files: `constants.ts`, `index.ts`, `types.ts`, optional `data/policy-*`

## Invariant A (adapter purity)

`KnowledgeSourceAdapter.listDocuments` returns plain `RawKnowledgeDocument` items only.
Adapters must not:
- write DB rows,
- call embedding functions,
- choose chunking strategy,
- influence ranking behavior.

Only `pipeline-commit-document.server.ts` may write `knowledge_document` or `knowledge_chunk`.

## Invariant B (retrieval is source-blind)

Retrieval and reranking paths must not branch on `knowledge_source.kind`.
Do not join source metadata for ranking heuristics.
Allowed retrieval inputs are tenant id, query, and optional explicit document allowlists.

## API / execution boundary

- Long-running sync/eval runs are durable workflows (`"use workflow"` / `"use step"`).
- Cron/Server Actions enqueue workflows and return quickly.
- Never run embedding/chunking loops inline in Route Handlers.
- JSONB metadata writes (`knowledge_eval_run.metadata`, credential metadata, sync metadata) must use typed contracts from `data/metadata-contracts.shared.ts`.
- BYOK crypto must remain centralized in `data/credential-cipher.server.ts` (`encryptCredential`, `decryptCredential` only).

## Imports

- Public imports from outside module: `#features/knowledge` only.
- Cross-module deep imports into `lib/features/knowledge/data/*` are forbidden.
